name: Testimonial Community Love Center - Food Distribution Center
review_text: My experience being at this shelter i was there for 6 months food was decent there was a smoke shop dispensary across the street lot of restaurants and grocery stores walking distance they staff were over all ok had some issues wit food being stolen on the women's side u get two drawers to keep ur belongings everything else u own has to fit under the bed any food in the cafeteria that u don't finish has to be thrown away u cant being it in ur dorm i didnt like like the food u bring to the dorm outside stays outside in the smoking area on the tables and after 9 pm it got thrown away if u have a service dog they have a dog play area and cages to keep ur pet on the women's side there is a winter shelter where the church is in the middle that is co ed men and woman and then a mens side bungalows at the end of the street I've had a friend who was on the mens side who got stabbed and they allowed that person to come back due to mental illness i don't think that is safe at all if u come here the sleeping arrangements are bunk beds two side for the women bouth 20 bucks on one side then bathroom is on the other side shared showers n toilets 8 bucks on the other side they have a clean up crew who comes every day round noon to clean u have to leave the dorm for bout an hr but after that u can go back to ur bed and lay down they have tvs in the door and a laundry room / break room every i believe tuesday or wednesday is Lennon day u wash ur Lennon every week And u can wash ur clothes til as early as 5am to 5 pm weekdays no washing clothes on weekends they have security on site who switch shifts every so often weekends are more chill u can watch tv in the day room just ask security to  turn on the tv curfew is 9 pm unless u work just give ur case manager ur work schedule and whenever u get off shouldn't be an issue if ur late for curfew i made aot of friends here seen people come n go move out got there housing some people get kicked out for not following the rules I've also made enemies my advise stay to ur self be careful who u hang out with keep an eye on ur stuff build a relationship with staff Speak up if u have issues cld uth don't get fed and u should be fine over all rate its a 8/10ðŸ¤—also posted some pictures of the food they give us for breakfast lunch and dinner girls side breakfast starts at 7 am if ur late u don't eat lunch grab n go sandwich chips 1 water bottle n fruit that's it dinner is at 5:30 If ur late u don't eat so make sure ur u stand in line wait for everyone to be called in hand sanitizer mask is optional U walk up u grab ur chair u sit down at 1 of two table n wait to be called do not just get up and walk up and grab a plate the lunch lady hates it when people do that I've got yelled at a couple times so just wait patiently for her to call your table that you can get up grab your plate walk over to the other table and there's condiments juice water fruit and then sit down and eat you have 30 minutes to eat and then the food has to be thrown away whatever you don't finish you cannot take food out of the cafeteria except for lunch I've gotten yelled at for taking food out the cafeteria overall just be cool with staff and you should be fun you can come and go as you please you don't have to stay there and you can do weekend passes overnight just got to ask your case manager ahead of time if I forgot anything feel free to comment any questions I'm happy to answer ask away
